  return <MDXLayout {...layoutProps} {...props} components={components} mdxType="MDXLayout">

    <p><strong parentName="p">{`⚠ THIS DOCUMENTATION IS INCOMPLETE!`}</strong></p>
    <p><img parentName="p" {...{
        "src": "assets/extensions/wifi/Items1.png",
        "alt": "WiFi Extension"
      }}></img></p>
    <p>{`The WiFi Extension Board can be programmed with Arduino, since a normal ESP8266 module is installed, which has a microcontroller integrated.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "design"
    }}>{`Design`}</h2>
    <p><img parentName="p" {...{
        "src": "assets/extensions/wifi/Items.png",
        "alt": "WiFi Extension"
      }}></img></p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`There is a UART interface for data transfer with the FPGA and there are 5 IOs on the module that can be used by the microcontroller, one of which is connected to an LED.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`Unlike normal ESP8266 boards, there are two buttons on the module needed to program the module. So you only need a USB to UART module to program the microcontroller`}</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "implementation"
    }}>{`Implementation`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "program-module"
    }}>{`Program module`}</h3>
    <p>{`You can use Arduino to program the microcontroller.`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`German Tutorial: `}<a href="https://itler.net/arduino-ide-fuer-die-programmierung-von-esp8266-chips-vorbereiten/" target="_blank">{`Arduino IDE für die Programmierung von ESP8266 Chips vorbereiten`}</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>{`With a UART interface you can then transfer data between the module and FPGA.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-arduino"
      }}>{`byte data[4] = {0x00, 0x01, 0x02, 0x03}; //Data to send

void setup(){
    Serial.begin(115200);   //Configure UART with 115200 Baud
}
void loop(){
    Serial.write(data, 4);  //Send data
    delay(1000);            //Send data again
}
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`The WLAN function can be used as shown in the many examples provided with the library:`}</p>
    <p><img parentName="p" {...{
        "src": "assets/extensions/wifi/Screen.png",
        "alt": "WiFi Example"
      }}></img></p>
    <p>{`Alternatively you can use Blynk:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul"><a href="https://www.instructables.com/id/Simple-Led-Control-With-Blynk-and-NodeMCU-Esp8266-/" target="_blank">Simple Led Control With Blynk</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul"><a href="https://examples.blynk.cc/?board=ESP8266&shield=ESP8266%20WiFi&example=More%2FDHT11" target="_blank">Example</a></li>
    </ul>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "communicate-with-fpga"
    }}>{`Communicate with FPGA`}</h3>
    <p>{`To program the module you have to do the following:
`}<img parentName="p" {...{
        "src": "assets/extensions/wifi/Items2.png",
        "alt": null
      }}></img>{`
`}<img parentName="p" {...{
        "src": "assets/extensions/wifi/Items3.png",
        "alt": null
      }}></img></p>
    <p>{`You will need an UART Interface to communicate with the FPGA:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-vhdp"
      }}>{`--CODE INCOMPLETE
`}</code></pre>

    </MDXLayout>;
}

